Load Testing
Purpose
To check how the application performs under expected normal user load.
Goal
Verify:
Response time
Throughput
Stability
Resource usage
Example
An ecommerce site normally supports:
5,000 concurrent users
We test system with:
5,000 users

to see whether APIs respond within SLA.

Real-Time Example

During normal shopping traffic:

Login API should respond within 2 sec.
Key Focus
Expected traffic
Normal business load
Performance benchmark
2. Stress Testing
Purpose

To check system behavior beyond its capacity limit.

Goal

Find:

Breaking point
Failure behavior
Recovery capability
Example

System capacity:

5,000 users

We gradually increase:

10,000
20,000 users

until application crashes or becomes unstable.

Real-Time Example

Big Billion Day sale overload.

Key Focus
Extreme load
System crash point
Recovery after failure
3. Spike Testing
Purpose

To check how application handles sudden sharp increase/decrease in traffic.

Goal

Verify:

Auto-scaling
Stability during traffic spikes
Recovery speed
Example

Suddenly increase:

100 users → 10,000 users within seconds
Real-Time Example

Concert ticket booking opening at 10 AM.

Key Focus
Sudden traffic burst
Rapid scaling
Sudden load changes
4. Soak Testing (Endurance Testing)
Purpose

To check system stability over a long duration under continuous load.

Goal

Find:

Memory leaks
Resource leaks
Performance degradation over time
Example

Run:

5,000 users continuously for 24–48 hours
Real-Time Example

Banking systems running continuously for days.

Key Focus
Long-duration stability
Memory leak detection
Resource exhaustion
Quick Comparison Table
Testing Type	Purpose	Load Pattern	Main Goal
Load Testing	Normal expected load	Gradual/steady	Check performance
Stress Testing	Beyond capacity	Increasing extreme load	Find breaking point
Spike Testing	Sudden traffic increase	Instant spike	Check scaling/stability
Soak Testing	Long duration load	Continuous steady load	Find memory/resource leaks
Easy Interview One-Line Definitions
Load Testing

Testing application under expected user load.

Stress Testing

Testing application beyond maximum capacity.

Spike Testing

Testing application with sudden traffic spikes.

Soak Testing

Testing application continuously for long duration.

Real Ecommerce Example
Scenario	Testing Type
Daily normal traffic	Load Testing
Black Friday overload	Stress Testing
Flash sale at 12 AM	Spike Testing
48-hour sale event	Soak Testing
